body.description: Scherber Professional Fully Stocked EMT/EMS Kit From practical to tactical - Scherber is serious about survival. Whether you’re a certified first responder, experienced paramedic, avid hiker or peewee soccer coach, safety and preparedness are always top priority. Take ‘just in case’ to new levels of precaution with a high-quality First Responder Bag from Scherber. Available in three distinct colors, this emergency essential delivers all the features you’d expect in a first response sack. Stock its plethora of pockets and compartments with all your go-to supplies and equipment—and save the day in style! Heavy-Duty 600D Polyester 8 Pockets & Compartments Strong Zipper Closures Padded Shoulder Strap Bright Reflective Striping

THE ULTIMATE FIRST RESPONSE SET Be Fully Stocked & Ready to Go in Case of Emergency! | High-Performance Trauma Kit Includes Everything Professionals Need to Protect & Serve with Confidence | Perfect for EMT, EMS, Fire, Police, Paramedics & Other Servicemen & Servicewomen

Indestructible Design Premium 600D polyester is thick, sturdy and strong, yet flexible enough to fling over your shoulder. Repels water, wind, dirt and dust. Maximum Visibility Tote your gear late at night without worry. Reflective webbing is woven around the bag. Exceptional Organization With (8) distinct pockets and interior compartments (dividers included), it’s not a bag, but a complete storage system. Snag-Proof Zippers We replaced the usual buckles with high-quality reflective zipper closures—perfect for accessing your gear in a pinch.

Versatile Tool Loops Top flap loops in various sizes, so you can securely tote shears, tweezers, hemostats and more. Comfy Shoulder Strap A removable carry strap lightens your load with a padded section positioned over the shoulder. Great for neck and back pain. Name Card Slot Slip your name or business card into the window—then wear it proudly! Built to Last If your bag fails for any reason, Scherber is on call 24/7 to make it right.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 28, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Wow very impressed, kit covers just about every emergency you will encounter. The nearest hospital is over 45 minutes away, this medic kit could be the difference in making it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 16, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Best made EMS bags I've seen. Designed for heavy use. Any first responder would be glad to have this in their home/vehicle. Supplies came well packaged and were EMS oriented. Quality supplies for any emergency large or small. Also purchased companies small color coded bags that are equally well made. Wish we had bags this well made when I was active in EMS.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Everything you need
reviews.reviewText: This is one of the most well stocked kits I have seen

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I took this to my local fire department...
reviews.reviewText: I took this to my local fire department and they were impressed. The only thing that they said the would add was some more latex gloves which they gave me a handful of.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great starter bag
reviews.reviewText: The only thing needed is a pulse ox and a glucose meter to complete the bag. Everything I need as a rural EMT

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 22, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very well stocked starter kit
reviews.reviewText: This is a very well-stocked base kit. I have added a few what I found to be missing critical items and medicine to really make this kit top-notch. Overall a good value for the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 15, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good to have
reviews.reviewText: Fully stocked. I live in the pacific northwest,if we have a major earthquake, the ability to stop the bleeding could mean the difference between life and death.Really happy to have this kit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 3, 2022
reviews.reviewText: This bag is perfect for my use as a firefighter/ EMR.
